    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="193" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d193">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Denby</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 21,
                                    1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1205.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 2390, of the 7th ultimo, incloses
                            copy of the imperial edict degrading the ex-viceroy, Liu Ping-chang, for
                            his connection with the Szechuan riots.</p>
                <p>The Department has read this edict with gratification. It is believed
                            that the punishment of the ex-viceroy will be a salutary example, and
                            that the punishment of all implicated subordinate officials is
                            practically pledged thereby.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
